metadata.name: Mooncakes: Happy Mid Autumn Festival 2022 #3513
metadata.description:
To celebrate the Moon Festival with Mooncakes, we have created a quest to introduce everyone to fxhash. As part of that quest on mooncakes.fun, users are encouraged to mint this generative token.

This is a layered image composition using the Mooncakes site images on a 1920x1080 canvas. The image elements are randomly assigned position, scale, tint, and blur according to a ruleset which generates a Mid Autumn Festival scene made up of: Moon, Clouds, Stars, Lanterns, and Lotuses.

Special filters, shapes and colors are included as rare features, as well as a couple of surprises.

metadata.name: Tezos Goons #281
metadata.description:
"When Humanity is in need, the Tezos Goons appear to fight the evil and aid the world..."


Tezos Goons is a pixel art PFP project that was created by the Greek Tezos community as a contribution to the collective effort to provide help for people affected by the devastating earthquake in Turkey and Syria through the #TezQuakeAid initiative. More info on the initiative can be found at https://app.joyn.xyz/contest/-tezquakeaid-gallery-a93c16832314

100% of the primary sales will go straight to the multi-sig contract that has been set up by @tezquakeaid and any royalties accumulated till the end of #TezQuakeAid will also be sent to the same contract to be used for the same cause.

"Tezos Goons" is a collective effort of the Tezos Greece community (https://twitter.com/Tezos_Gr).

The artwork of the project was created by the community member @MrEvdilos (https://twitter.com/MrEvdilos)

and the technical part was implemented by @mtsirides1 (https://twitter.com/mtsirides1) using @PureSpider's template. We thank them all for their kind contributions and their voluntary efforts!


For the Project:

Each Tezos Goon is randomly generated and has 7 traits (Background, Weapons, Bodies, Clothing, Mouth, Eyes, Headtop) from a total of 130 different options.

Another 6 "Legendary" animated Goons will be minted as a separate collection on Objkt and 5 of them will be given away to Tezos Goons holders through a raffle. Each goon that you mint (and hold) is 1 entry in the raffle. The 6th Legendary Goon will be auctioned for the same cause (#TezQualeAid).

metadata.name: Enfold #8
metadata.description:
“We saw the first blossoms late that year, an anticipated promise from the tenacious, etiolated fingers we'd observed making their way through the unseasonable snow; a dirty snow. They represented hope, pushing through this gritty crust formed of equal parts ice and ash making an inevitable descent from the troposphere. We kidded ourselves it was the earth washing itself clean, erasing all evidence of what we'd done, though we knew in our secret hearts that no amount of rainfall, ironically, could save us from the flood.”

Enfold is a piece based around distance: distance from circles, distance from centres, distance from edges. Points, places and relationships between separate entities are combined and forced through curated palettes of bright and vivid colours, producing overlapping, elliptical and lens-shaped areas formed from emergent, convex arcs.

metadata.name: Skies and Lands #80
metadata.description:
Skies and Lands is a collection of generative art featuring a house as the protagonist in an endless array of distinct landscapes. Each piece in the collection showcases a unique representation of the house located in different lands, with varied and dramatic skies providing a captivating contrast. The combination of the static architecture with the constantly changing landscape creates a stunning and never-before-seen visual experience. "Skies and Lands" collection invites the viewer to explore new perspectives and to enjoy the beauty of architecture and nature together. A timeless work of art that will undoubtedly delight art and nature lovers alike.

Don't miss the chance to own a piece of this unique and captivating collection.

metadata.name: Another Perspective #2 #51
metadata.description:
This work was made using reverse perspective projection.
Perspective projection is common in traditional Western painting and 3D computer graphics.
However, it is not always necessary to use it, as in this work.

Drag the screen to change the camera angle.

Made with Three.js

metadata.name: Scattered Pathways #310
metadata.description:
"Scattered Pathways" studies pathfinding on a grid. I enjoy watching the sketch find and fill the available spaces. I hope you enjoy this one too!

Royalties Splits:
50% Donation to minter

Features:
Two different sizes: 12x18", 12x12"
Portrait or landscape orientation
~500 color pallets, one black and white, one cyan, magenta, yellow and black, and the rest from Jam3/nice-color-palettes.

Dependencies:
processing/p5.js
lodash/lodash
Jam3/nice-color-palettes
@liamegan1/fxhash-helpers
@altesc/stdio

Export to a PNG format at several different sizes.
- Press s: save the current render size
- Press t: scale to screen size
- Press f: full print size (see features for dimensions)

License: CC-BY

Please find me on Twitter and Instagram at @natenolting.

metadata.name: Gravity's End #40
metadata.description:
Gravity's End depicts fictional worlds being warped, distorted, and in rare cases, shattered, due to extreme gravitational forces.

Gravity's End is written with shaders, so a gpu is recommended. It is very gpu friendly, in that only one frame is rendered.

Rarities

- 21 palettes with 5 rare palettes (4% chance for rare).
- 10% chance of getting a shattered world.

Keys: 

's' saves a png in the exact size of the screen.

metadata.name: Beacon #100
metadata.description:
Thousands of glowing beams, each with its own gradient and disappearing to a path of vanishing points. While the inspiration was figurative, drawn from the Northern Lights, the results have been taken to the abstract. Bold shapes in the foreground draw focus and their simple geometries are elevated to a signal. 

This project was created during a Speed Run over ~24 hours.
Uses WEBGL and may load a little slowly on some machines.

metadata.name: zancannabis #129
metadata.description:
zancannabis is a celebration of 4/20 2023 and is of course a respectful parody of the artwork from the legend that is zancan.
this artwork uses code to randomly place illustrations of cannabis plants created using midjourney ai with post-production in Illustrator and Photoshop.

The work is in no way related to the artist zancan and is not intended to fool anyone into thinking so thus does not affect the original artists market or value.

metadata.name: Annum #373
metadata.description:
This project is being released in celebration of the 1 year aniversary of Achromat, my first release on fxhash. In addition to being inspired by Achromat, aspects of other previous projects have been incorporated. My deepest gratitude to all who have collected my work over the past year.

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.

50% of primary sales go to Savepakistan.

metadata.name: NAKACHOII #435
metadata.description:
*Nakachoii*
The Nakachoii soldiers from anime lands entered fxhash, this time to get new faces and new powers with the coding that is applied to them. Every time they are minted, and every time a new hash is generated, a new power is given to them. The Nakachoii soldier will fit inside your wallet and protect it with these powers. We are very happy that we gained so much experience on fxhash during its first year, and finally, we were able to create a great project based on all these experiences. Nakachoii is ready to create beauty.

metadata.name: Why? #106
metadata.description:
The direction taken by the artwork Why? was taken when contemplating a canvas filled with what could be viewed as huge stone steps. I added the small stick people - were they climbing up or down? Where were they going? Where did they come from?
I then became interested in how subtle changes of background colour and changes of balloon colour changed the story, or the feeling of the story - ranging from bright hope to despair and futility. 

All p5.js.
The artwork is rendered at window size, use keys '2' and '3' to render larger.

metadata.name: Crisis Worlds #136
metadata.description:
An abstract, generative illustration of impending planetary doom. Something, or someone, has sent the gas giants of the galaxy on a path toward destruction.

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 2318 × 3000px
Press ’p’ to pause/resume.

Less common features
- Giant planets
- Inverted, light colors
- Umber/grey and mint green as the primary space colors
- Star trails are 50/50

metadata.description: simple shape, simple shadow

metadata.name: O Fortuna #61
metadata.description:
"O Fortuna
Velut Luna
Statu variabilis

Semper crescis
Aut decrescis
Vita detestabilis
Nunc obdurat
Et tunc curat
Ludo mentis aciem
Egestatem
Potestatem
Dissolvit ut glaciem

Sors immanis
Et inanis
Rota tu volubilis"

As in the story of "Carmina Burana: O Fortuna", nothing is permanent, everything fluctuates, an emotional rollercoaster, sometimes up, sometimes down. The present situation should not define you, as your circumstances are ever-changing and uncertain. Remember that tomorrow is a new day and with it comes new opportunities for growth and improvement.

[S] to save a image file

made with p5.js , p5.js.noise
2023

metadata.name: pointillism in lines  #50
metadata.description:
This painting is drawn in pointillism style.
which includes 14 layers.
The first 10 layers contain pointillism drawings and the 11th layer is the patterns of each line.
In the 12th layer, there are 30 covers made of different geometric shapes and brushes.
And noise and frames are used in the last two layers.

metadata.name: Folding Progressions #12
metadata.description:
A minimalist composition based on quad strips, transparencies and a constrained color palette
that produce simulations of volumetric structures.

My first Gentk of the year 2023.

Coded with p5.js
by josemiguel.tez
2023
